The Activity Completed trigger activates the flow when a specific activity is marked as completed.**Topics Covered:**[How to Configure Activity Completed Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/36768417301401-Activity-Completed#h_01J7WRJJ536K5HG4NDS50EKYR2)[Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/36768417301401-Activity-Completed#h_01J7WSC93DD4BX6K4RKD47R1E6)

### How to Configure Activity Completed Trigger

While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Activity Completed**Trigger.

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-3.png)

Once selected, you would then need to configure the block.As you click on the block, a pop will open to add following details.**Name:**Provide a clear and descriptive name for the trigger to easily identify its purpose.**Description:**Enter a brief explanation of what the trigger does and its role in the flow.**Type:**Specify the type of activity (e.g., meeting, call, task) that will activate the trigger upon completion.**Owner:**Select the owner of the activity or the person responsible for the follow-up actions.**Outcome:**Define the desired outcome or result that will trigger the flow.Â Once done, hit on**Save**.

![mceclip1.png](./images/mceclip1-2.png)

### Practical Example

####**Setup next followup**Whenever a salesperson tries to followup a customer and hits voicemail or busy status, then completing that activity will auto-create a new followup activity for the next day so that a lead doesn't fall through the crack.

![mceclip0(1).png](./images/mceclip01-2.png)

####**Auto update/move deal stage**Suppose you have got a new deal and you need to verify the lead's submitted data and their requirement. As soon as you complete the first follow-up activity with the status connected, the deal's stage is auto-updated from New to Qualified.
